---

## Agent Behavior Rules (mandatory — follow every session)

1. READ `context/` folder before writing any code.
2. READ `context/aria_failures.md` before ANY Fusion or CadQuery CAD work.
3. PLAN in plain English BEFORE generating code — state the steps out loud.
4. Never hardcode geometry — all constants live in `context/aria_mechanical.md`.
5. Never bypass STM32 safety layer logic under any circumstance.
6. Every constant in `tools/aria_simulator.py` MUST match `firmware/stm32/aria_main.cpp`.
7. Fusion scripts MUST use Direct Design mode (no Parametric). Solid box first → cut interior → features on faces. Never use annular profile extrusion (known failure).
8. After each session: write a brief log to `sessions/YYYY-MM-DD_task.md`.
9. On failure: diagnose, update `context/aria_failures.md`, retry — do NOT ask user unless retried 3x.
10. If retried 3x without success: write diagnosis to `sessions/` and stop with summary.

---

## Hardware Architecture

| Component | Role |
|---|---|
| STM32F411 Black Pill | Safety layer: watchdog, fault detection, clutch control, brake GPIO, VESC UART |
| XIAO ESP32-S3 Sense | Intelligence: voice (Edge Impulse), CV (camera), BLE, UART → STM32 |
| Makerbase VESC MINI 6.7 | FOC motor driver (UART from STM32, NOT SimpleFOC on STM32) |
| 57mm BLDC + 30:1 planetary | Slack management, 24V, power-off brake |
| HX711 + 50kg load cell | Rope tension via sheave reaction force |
| AS5048A magnetic encoder | Spool position / payout (SPI to STM32) |
| Centrifugal clutch | 200mm brake drum, primary fall arrest (Lead Solo design) — mechanical, zero electronics |
| Rope spool | 600mm, 6061 Al housing, wall-mounted behind panel |
| E-stop (40mm NC twist-release) | Hardware emergency stop in series with brake circuit |
| nRF52 + PDM mic (wearable) | Harness BLE mic for climber voice commands |

**Fail-safe principle:** ESP32 crash → STM32 holds safe tension. STM32/VESC fault → brake engages; clutch catches mechanically. Power cut → power-off brake + clutch controls descent.

---

## System States

IDLE → CLIMBING → CLIPPING → CLIMBING
↓ voice/sensor
TAKE | REST | LOWER | WATCH_ME | UP
↓ fault / E-stop
CLIMBING_PAUSED (zone intrusion 10s) → EMERGENCY_STOP

text

| State | Motor/Brake | Exit |
|---|---|---|
| IDLE | Brake on | CV climber + tension > 15N |
| CLIMBING | PID tension 40N | Voice or clip detected |
| CLIPPING | Pre-pay slack | Auto after clip duration |
| TAKE | Lock spool | "climbing" or upward movement |
| REST | Hold position | "climbing" or timeout |
| LOWER | Controlled payout | Tension < 15N |
| WATCH_ME | Tighter tension | "climbing" or timeout |
| UP | Near-zero tension | "climbing" or timeout |
| CLIMBING_PAUSED | Brake on, hold | Zone cleared or "climbing" |
| EMERGENCY_STOP | Brake on | Power cycle only |

---

## Critical Safety Constraints

- STM32 safety layer is NEVER bypassed — all state transitions validated there
- TAKE requires: voice confidence > 85% AND load cell > 200N within 500ms window
- Fall detection: rope speed > 2.0 m/s AND tension > 400N → motor → 0%, clutch takes over
- Load cell > 8000N → immediate ESTOP
- ESP32 comms lost > 2s → STM32 goes to safe hold mode automatically
- Static SF < 1.5 → hard failure (CEM). SF 1.5–2.0 → warning. SF ≥ 2.0 → pass.

---

## Key Constants (always sync these between files)

```python
TENSION_BASELINE_N         = 40.0    # climbing tension target
TENSION_TAKE_THRESHOLD_N   = 200.0   # load cell minimum to confirm TAKE
TENSION_FALL_THRESHOLD_N   = 400.0   # fall detection trigger
CLIP_DETECT_CONFIDENCE     = 0.75    # CV clip gesture minimum
VOICE_CONFIDENCE_MIN       = 0.85    # Edge Impulse voice minimum
TAKE_CONFIRM_WINDOW_MS     = 500     # ms to confirm TAKE with load cell
ROPE_SPEED_FALL_MS         = 2.0     # m/s rope speed for fall detect
PID_KP = 2.5 / PID_KI = 0.8 / PID_KD = 0.1